1
00:01:06,710 --> 00:01:08,310
如果我们遂了他的愿
If we give him what he wants...

2
00:01:08,310 --> 00:01:12,370
如果我们按厄舍的意思任命法官  那就完了
If we give Usher what he says, his justice, that is it.

3
00:01:12,370 --> 00:01:14,750
彻底完了  我们就被他拿住了
It's over. He owns us.

4
00:01:14,750 --> 00:01:17,450
-别小题大做  -是倒好了
- Don't exaggerate. - I wish I were.

5
00:01:17,450 --> 00:01:19,220
这样的交易你做过上千次了
You've made a thousand deals.

6
00:01:19,220 --> 00:01:20,690
这次不一样
Yeah, well, this one is different.

7
00:01:20,690 --> 00:01:23,470
-怎么不一样  -因为我能感觉到
- Why? - Because I can feel it right here.

8
00:01:23,670 --> 00:01:25,850
-你听见自己在说什么了吗  -清清楚楚
- Do you hear yourself? - Yeah, loud and clear.

9
00:01:25,850 --> 00:01:29,320
我倒有点奇怪你似乎一个字都没听见
I'm a little confused that you don't seem to hear me at all.

10
00:01:29,970 --> 00:01:32,080
只要我们真正夺回权力
Once we're solidly back in power,

11
00:01:32,080 --> 00:01:34,060
-我们就能恢复职位...  -幼稚
- we will regain our position... - That is naive.

12
00:01:34,060 --> 00:01:35,650
你从来没这么幼稚过
Naive is new for you.

13
00:01:36,130 --> 00:01:37,870
我这是现实  不是幼稚
Realistic. Not naive.

14
00:01:37,870 --> 00:01:40,070
我们奋斗的一切成果  都会烟消云散
Everything we've worked for, we can kiss it goodbye.

15
00:01:40,070 --> 00:01:42,770
我们同意让厄舍来挑人  没得商量
We agreed to Usher's pick. It's non-negotiable.

16
00:01:42,770 --> 00:01:46,540
说得太对了  他挑人  他的法官
That's exactly right. It's his pick. It's his justice.

17
00:01:46,540 --> 00:01:49,800
他想控制我们的政府  我们的白宫
He's trying to control our house. The White House.

18
00:01:49,800 --> 00:01:52,280
我向他保证过了  弗兰西斯
I gave him my word, Francis.

19
00:01:53,490 --> 00:01:55,040
你保证
Your word?

20
00:01:55,710 --> 00:01:59,340
你保证  这场谈话真是毫无意义
Your word? This conversation is pointless.

21
00:01:59,340 --> 00:02:00,610
成熟点吧
Grow up!

22
00:02:01,860 --> 00:02:03,080
你以为你是谁
Who do you think you are?

23
00:02:03,080 --> 00:02:05,170
我以为我是临时代总统
I think I am a temporary president

24
00:02:05,170 --> 00:02:06,660
想帮你夺回宝座
trying to get you back in office.

25
00:02:06,660 --> 00:02:09,770
如果你不认为眼下是我们至关重要的关口
And if you don't think that we're at a critical juncture in the road,

26
00:02:09,770 --> 00:02:12,050
那你真是错得可悲
you are pathetically mistaken.

27
00:02:12,220 --> 00:02:14,740
醒醒吧  克莱尔  醒醒吧
Wake up, Claire! Wake up!

