{\an2}{\pos(208.1,242.25)}第五季  第七集

46
00:04:11,040 --> 00:04:12,550
这是欧洲东部时间今早
Recorded this morning EET

47
00:04:12,560 --> 00:04:15,330
在大马士革亚默克区拍到的
in the Yarmouk neighborhood of Damascus.

48
00:04:19,830 --> 00:04:23,020
看来他在剑桥期间喜欢上吃巧克力了
Seems he developed a taste for chocolate while at Cambridge.

49
00:04:24,620 --> 00:04:27,150
画面上这位是艾哈迈德·艾哈迈迪
Smiling for the camera is Ahmed Al Ahmadi,

50
00:04:27,150 --> 00:04:28,490
尤瑟夫的兄弟
Yusuf's brother.

51
00:04:29,760 --> 00:04:31,070
你确定吗
Are you sure?

52
00:04:31,870 --> 00:04:34,060
我和尤瑟夫·艾哈迈迪谈了很久
I had a long conversation with Yusuf Al Ahmadi.

53
00:04:34,060 --> 00:04:35,670
他们俩完全不像
They look nothing alike.

54
00:04:36,210 --> 00:04:37,450
就是他
It's him.

55
00:04:39,760 --> 00:04:41,650
艾哈迈德还在我们监控中吗
Is Ahmed still in our sights?

56
00:04:41,700 --> 00:04:44,080
-是的  -这个机会非常难得
- He is. - This is a rare opportunity.

57
00:04:44,110 --> 00:04:46,090
我们应该趁机发动定点袭击
We should seize the moment and make a targeted strike.

58
00:04:46,090 --> 00:04:48,300
-总监  得了吧  -总统女士
- Director, please. - Madam President...

59
00:04:48,300 --> 00:04:50,660
有什么问题吗  将军
Is there some issue, General?

60
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:56,190
艾哈迈德·艾哈迈迪不可能大老远地
Ahmed Al Ahmadi didn't travel all the way

61
00:04:56,190 --> 00:04:58,910
从他的据点跑到大马士革就为了买糖吃
from his compound to Damascus to buy a candy bar.

62
00:04:58,910 --> 00:05:01,200
他肯定要见什么人  我们应该查清是谁
He's meeting with someone. Let's find out who.

63
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:03,950
可这样他可能会被我们惊动  就此消失
Unless we're detected, and he disappears for good.

64
00:05:03,950 --> 00:05:05,210
可我们只要等一等
But if we wait,

65
00:05:05,210 --> 00:05:08,110
就非常有可能了解更多哈里发国的情报
there's a huge potential to learn more about ICO.

66
00:05:08,110 --> 00:05:11,260
它的成员  联系人  行动规律和战术
Its members, contacts, habits, tactics.

67
00:05:11,700 --> 00:05:14,540
你今天早上真是一反常态地
You know, you're sounding uncharacteristically dovish

68
00:05:14,540 --> 00:05:16,120
保守啊  将军
this morning, General.

69
00:05:18,180 --> 00:05:20,210
我同意布雷格将军的看法
I agree with General Braegher.

70
00:05:20,340 --> 00:05:23,000
虽然对艾哈迈迪发动精确空袭
While a successful air strike against Ahmadi

71
00:05:23,000 --> 00:05:25,900
-会非常有利于  -这跟选举无关  凯茜
- would play well... - This isn't about the election, Cathy.

72
00:05:26,310 --> 00:05:29,620
当然没关系  我是说  只要我们手段得当
No, of course not. I mean, if we do this correctly,

73
00:05:29,620 --> 00:05:32,630
我们就可以逐步瓦解哈里发国的网络
we can begin the process of dismantling ICO's network.

74
00:05:32,630 --> 00:05:33,900
干掉他
Take him out.

75
00:05:35,290 --> 00:05:36,960
如果总统同意的话
If the president agrees,

76
00:05:36,960 --> 00:05:39,170
我认为这对国家最有利
I think it's the best thing for the country.

77
00:05:39,990 --> 00:05:42,680
我觉得这会给哈里发国发出非常明确的信号
Well, I think it would send a very clear message to ICO.

78
00:05:42,680 --> 00:05:44,250
短期来看没错  但是
In the short term, yes, but...

79
00:05:44,270 --> 00:05:47,110
短期没错就够了
No other term is relevant.

80
00:05:50,320 --> 00:05:51,790
我觉得我们已经在
I think we have been operating

81
00:05:51,790 --> 00:05:53,970
恐怖主义的阴影下忍受太久了
under the shadow of terror for too long.

82
00:05:53,970 --> 00:05:56,820
为了美国人民  我们必须采取坚决行动
For the sake of the American people, we need to act now.

83
00:05:56,950 --> 00:05:58,690
预计需要多长时间  将军
What's the timetable, General?

84
00:05:59,390 --> 00:06:02,370
只要目标位置准确  几个小时就行
For an actionable location, most likely a number of hours.

85
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:03,810
谢谢
Thank you.

86
00:06:06,230 --> 00:06:08,200
你这是在浪费我们的时间
You're wasting our time.

87
00:06:08,210 --> 00:06:10,320
我们要讲究他在哪以何种面貌出现
We're being selective about where and how he appears.

88
00:06:10,320 --> 00:06:11,920
很快他就什么活动都不能参加了
Soon he won't be at any events at all.

89
00:06:11,920 --> 00:06:14,350
汉娜  我们只是想尽力把他和你送入白宫
Hannal, we're just trying to land him and you in the White House.

90
00:06:14,350 --> 00:06:18,500
不是布洛哈特-康威  马克  是康威在前
And it's not Brockhart-Conway, Mark. It's the opposite.

91
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:21,510
他肯定忍不了多久
He won't put up with this much longer.

92
00:06:21,510 --> 00:06:22,640
我知道他一定很难受
I know, I'm sure it's hard on him.

93
00:06:22,640 --> 00:06:23,910
我得接这个电话  抱歉
I have to take this. I'm sorry.

94
00:06:23,920 --> 00:06:25,860
他到那儿之后会怎么样
What happens after he gets there?

95
00:06:25,900 --> 00:06:29,150
-威尔会怎么样  -我们会支持他
- To Will? What happens? - We'll be there for him.

96
00:06:29,150 --> 00:06:31,550
-你和布洛哈特将军  -对
- You and General Brockhart? - Yes.

97
00:06:32,630 --> 00:06:34,180
威尔是什么角色
What will Will's role be?

98
00:06:36,210 --> 00:06:38,420
我会继续支持你丈夫
I will continue to support your husband.

99
00:06:38,660 --> 00:06:42,060
给我一个真正的答案  你欠我的
Give me a real answer. You owe me that.

100
00:06:42,940 --> 00:06:45,690
他的角色将是美国总统
His role will be President of the United States.

101
00:06:54,720 --> 00:06:56,830
麦克风还开着  布洛哈特脱口而出
The mic was still hot and Brockhart just kept talking.

102
00:06:56,830 --> 00:06:59,160
-她是这么说的  -抗命吗
- That's what she said. - Insubordination?

103
00:07:00,020 --> 00:07:02,960
-她用的是这个词吗  -她听着是这意思
- That's the word she used? - It's what it sounded like to her.

104
00:07:02,960 --> 00:07:06,150
他在谈士兵  他说
He was talking about soldiers and he said, quote,

105
00:07:06,150 --> 00:07:08,510
"我第一个站出来让军人抗命"
"I'll be the first to tell them not to listen."

106
00:07:08,510 --> 00:07:11,410
-她能不能弄到真正的录音  -是有代价的
- Can she get her hands on the actual clip? - For a price.

107
00:07:11,580 --> 00:07:14,020
-我还以为她是朋友  -对  聪明的朋友
- I thought she was a friend. - Yeah, a smart friend.

108
00:07:14,020 --> 00:07:16,630
这是一条很不错的辩论后30秒广告
It's a nice 30-second spot, post-debate.

109
00:07:16,630 --> 00:07:17,970
如果有辩论的话
If there is a debate.

110
00:07:19,260 --> 00:07:20,870
攻击他们的长处
Hits them at their strength.

111
00:07:21,010 --> 00:07:23,560
动摇他们的军事公信力
Takes the military credibility away.

112
00:07:24,470 --> 00:07:27,320
这种东西能反转大选结果
This is the kind of thing that can turn an election.

113
00:07:29,090 --> 00:07:33,230
不管要付出什么代价  都值了
Whatever this costs... it's worth it.

114
00:07:36,670 --> 00:07:38,660
我们把它搞到手  证实一下
Let's secure it and then verify it.

115
00:07:42,180 --> 00:07:45,250
不管是不是休会任命本森大法官
Recess appointment of Judge Benson or no,

116
00:07:45,250 --> 00:07:48,920
得让人们继续关注田纳西和俄亥俄的重新投票
people need to stay focused on the revote in Tennessee and Ohio

117
00:07:48,920 --> 00:07:50,630
以及我们为何走到这一步
and how the hell we got here.

118
00:07:50,880 --> 00:07:52,070
好
All right.

119
00:07:52,910 --> 00:07:55,340
我让助理安吉拉联系你
I'll have my assistant Angela reach out

120
00:07:55,340 --> 00:07:57,570
看你什么时候需要我去录影棚
to confirm what time you need me at the studio.

121
00:07:58,680 --> 00:08:02,570
好  好的
All right. Yep. Yeah.

122
00:08:04,980 --> 00:08:06,460
我把道格·斯坦普被劫车那天
I collected everything I could find

123
00:08:06,460 --> 00:08:08,840
能查到的资料都搜集齐了
about the day Doug Stamper was carjacked.

124
00:08:08,850 --> 00:08:10,000
好
Good.

125
00:08:10,320 --> 00:08:11,740
好了  那么
All right, so...

126
00:08:13,340 --> 00:08:14,790
是在哪
where was that?

127
00:08:16,810 --> 00:08:18,480
在哪发生的
Where that happened?

128
00:08:19,630 --> 00:08:21,670
在马里兰
In Maryland.

129
00:08:23,500 --> 00:08:26,240
就在
Right around, um...

130
00:08:26,300 --> 00:08:29,030
我是在离那儿半小时车程的地方长大的
Yeah, I grew up about a half an hour from there...

131
00:08:29,230 --> 00:08:31,400
在这里
It's here.

132
00:08:33,940 --> 00:08:36,790
瑞秋·波斯纳的
And Rachel Posner's...

133
00:08:38,000 --> 00:08:41,140
最后已知地址
last known address.

134
00:08:56,640 --> 00:08:58,860
也就15分钟路程
I'd say they were about 15 minutes apart.

135
00:09:05,490 --> 00:09:08,610
我不知道我为什么要跟你解释
I'm not sure why I need to explain myself to you.

136
00:09:08,610 --> 00:09:10,050
你为什么要去国安局
Why would you go to the NSA?

137
00:09:10,050 --> 00:09:13,920
我想调查一名美国公民是否安然无恙
I was inquiring into the well-being of an American citizen.

138
00:09:14,220 --> 00:09:16,320
他就是个心怀不满的黑客而已
He's just a disgruntled hacker.

139
00:09:16,320 --> 00:09:18,510
那你为什么对他这么感兴趣呢
Then why are you so interested in him?

140
00:09:21,570 --> 00:09:22,880
他看上去怎么样
How did he look?

141
00:09:23,490 --> 00:09:25,010
我是为了我自己问的
I'm asking for me.

142
00:09:25,100 --> 00:09:26,920
我13岁就认识艾丹了
I've known Aidan since I was 13 years old.

143
00:09:26,920 --> 00:09:29,180
他和我妈妈曾交往过几年
He and my mom dated for several years.

144
00:09:29,190 --> 00:09:30,650
当然  那是很久之前了
Was a long time ago, obviously.

145
00:09:30,920 --> 00:09:33,610
但他并不想要国安局那份工作
But as far as the NSA job, he didn't want it.

146
00:09:33,610 --> 00:09:34,940
是我逼他接受的
I made him take it.

147
00:09:36,540 --> 00:09:41,070
我不明白他们怎么找到他的  他为什么在那儿
I don't understand how they got him or why he's there.

148
00:09:41,070 --> 00:09:43,680
我需要知道他是安全的
I need to know that he is safe.

149
00:09:44,250 --> 00:09:45,700
他看上去还行
He looked fine.

150
00:09:48,370 --> 00:09:50,050
他知道什么  莉安
What does he know, LeAnn?

151
00:09:50,550 --> 00:09:52,710
也许跟你我知道的差不多
Probably about the same as you and me,

152
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:56,300
所以我们不能让他惹上严重的麻烦
which is why we need to keep him out of any serious trouble.

153
00:10:01,860 --> 00:10:05,740
我不想涉足你的私生活  莉安
I don't want to get involved in your personal life, LeAnn.

154
00:10:06,610 --> 00:10:08,460
-我是来见总统的  -当然
- I'm here to see the president. - Of course.

155
00:10:08,460 --> 00:10:09,730
但你仔细想想  凯茜
But when you think about it, Cathy,

156
00:10:09,730 --> 00:10:11,580
我们都脱不了干系
we're all sort of involved here.

157
00:10:12,460 --> 00:10:15,780
如果他有危险  他是无法承受的
If he is in any kind of danger, he is not built for it.

158
00:10:15,780 --> 00:10:17,140
你好  凯茜
Hi, Cathy.

159
00:10:18,830 --> 00:10:20,050
简
Jane.

160
00:10:22,020 --> 00:10:25,260
莉安·哈维  简·戴维斯  简是副部长
LeAnn Harvey, Jane Davis. Jane is under secretary--

161
00:10:25,260 --> 00:10:29,040
商务部副助理部长  负责国际贸易
Deputy under secretary of commerce for international trade.

162
00:10:29,040 --> 00:10:29,860
很拗口
It's a mouthful.

163
00:10:29,860 --> 00:10:31,740
很高兴见到你本人
Yeah, it's good to put a face to the voice.

164
00:10:32,430 --> 00:10:34,240
你有布洛芬吗
Uh, do you have any ibuprofen?

165
00:10:34,310 --> 00:10:36,230
-我好像有阿司匹林  -不行
- Oh, I might have some aspirin. - No.

166
00:10:37,320 --> 00:10:39,730
-我过敏  会起疹子  -我们好像有
- I'm allergic. Gives me hives. - We may have some.

167
00:10:42,640 --> 00:10:46,340
你家就是做轮胎的哈维家族  对吧
You're the Harveys of the tire company, yes?

168
00:10:48,380 --> 00:10:51,560
我父亲和叔叔二十年前卖了公司
My father and uncle sold the business 20 years ago.

169
00:10:51,840 --> 00:10:53,960
之后胎面就不一样了
And the treads haven't been the same since.

170
00:10:56,540 --> 00:10:59,450
但很不错  你还是来到了华府
But it's great. You finally landed in D.C.

171
00:11:00,050 --> 00:11:02,290
我会告诉总统你们俩都来了
I'll let the president know you're both here.

172
00:11:02,310 --> 00:11:03,740
谢谢你的药
Uh, thank you for this.

173
00:11:09,660 --> 00:11:12,400
我们对调这两句就行了
Let's just reverse those two sentences and it's there.

174
00:11:12,400 --> 00:11:13,760
切中要点
It's to the point.

175
00:11:14,610 --> 00:11:17,890
-凝练  -没错  凝练
- Pithy. - Yes, pithy.

176
00:11:19,890 --> 00:11:21,210
她们来了
Your meeting is here.

177
00:11:23,490 --> 00:11:24,680
谢谢
Thank you.

178
00:11:25,340 --> 00:11:26,850
本森法官正在前往
And Justice Benson is en route

179
00:11:26,850 --> 00:11:28,420
白宫参与宣布仪式
to the White House for the announcement.

180
00:11:28,420 --> 00:11:30,350
我会让她在黄色椭圆厅等
I'll have her wait in the Yellow Oval.

181
00:11:31,030 --> 00:11:33,310
好  让她们进来  行吗
Uh, great. Can you send the others in, please?

182
00:11:33,410 --> 00:11:34,600
好的
Of course.

183
00:11:36,660 --> 00:11:38,770
前总统也会去玫瑰园吗
Is the former president meeting us in the Rose Garden?

184
00:11:38,770 --> 00:11:40,530
弗兰西斯不去
Francis will not be there.

185
00:11:42,360 --> 00:11:43,620
他不必去
He's not needed.

186
00:11:50,030 --> 00:11:51,430
戴维斯女士
Miss Davis.

187
00:11:51,660 --> 00:11:53,200
杜兰特国务卿
Secretary Durant.

188
00:11:55,120 --> 00:11:58,690
-好久不见  -是啊  上次见面是在哪
- It's been a long time. - Yes, where was that?

189
00:11:58,910 --> 00:12:02,100
阿斯彭一家智库  2000年初
A think tank in Aspen, early 2000.

190
00:12:02,600 --> 00:12:05,050
那时还有很多"智慧的火花"
Oh, there was a lot of thinking happening back then.

191
00:12:05,230 --> 00:12:07,050
还好我们阻止了
I'm glad we put a stop to that.

192
00:12:07,760 --> 00:12:09,090
请坐
Please, have a seat.

193
00:12:09,480 --> 00:12:11,400
我看过了与北京的
So, I've gone over the numbers

194
00:12:11,410 --> 00:12:14,500
钢铁协议的草案数据
of the proposed agreement of steel with Beijing

195
00:12:14,500 --> 00:12:16,560
我有些问题想问你
and I have a couple of questions for you.

196
00:12:16,560 --> 00:12:18,550
总统女士  我们需要带你撤离
Madam President, we need to evacuate you now.

197
00:12:18,550 --> 00:12:19,290
怎么回事
What's going on?

198
00:12:19,290 --> 00:12:20,990
请撤离  总统女士  是紧急情况
Please, Madam President. It's urgent.

199
00:12:21,070 --> 00:12:22,210
女士
Ma'am.

200
00:12:24,370 --> 00:12:25,380
你们要带我去哪
Where are you taking me?

201
00:12:25,380 --> 00:12:27,680
-将您转移到总统紧急行动中心  -为什么
- We're moving you to the PEOC. - Why?

202
00:12:27,940 --> 00:12:29,370
他们会在下面告诉您  女士
They'll brief you down below, ma'am.

203
00:12:29,370 --> 00:12:30,640
弗兰西斯人呢
Where's Francis?

204
00:12:52,960 --> 00:12:55,040
道格·斯坦普呢  还有耶茨先生呢
Where's Doug Stamper? And Mr. Yates?

205
00:12:55,040 --> 00:12:56,590
我们在照章办事  女士
We're following protocol, ma'am.

206
00:12:56,700 --> 00:12:59,080
国家安全顾问卡弗蒂在路上了
National Security Advisor Cafferty is on her way.

207
00:13:00,560 --> 00:13:02,740
-女士  -不  我们等弗兰西斯
- Ma'am? - No, we'll wait for Francis.

208
00:13:02,740 --> 00:13:03,700
他会在里面与您会合
He'll meet you inside.

209
00:13:03,700 --> 00:13:05,940
我们要等弗兰西斯  这是命令
We will wait for Francis. That's an order.

210
00:13:05,940 --> 00:13:07,850
-总统女士  -卡弗蒂女士  怎么回事
- Madam President. - Miss Cafferty, what's going on?

211
00:13:07,860 --> 00:13:09,010
尚无确切消息
Nothing's confirmed yet,

212
00:13:09,010 --> 00:13:12,370
但一辆携带放射性物质的卡车失踪了
but a truck carrying radioactive material has gone missing.

213
00:13:15,520 --> 00:13:18,090
-这是真的吗  -我们得和格林谈谈
- Is this real? - We have to talk to Green.

214
00:13:18,130 --> 00:13:19,450
我们进去吧
Let's head inside.

215
00:13:56,040 --> 00:13:57,140
是
Yes.

216
00:14:03,250 --> 00:14:06,110
我明白了  谢谢
I see. Thank you.

217
00:14:08,380 --> 00:14:10,190
国土安全部收到网络司令部的消息
Homeland received word from Cybercom

218
00:14:10,190 --> 00:14:13,740
一辆携带三台铯137辐照器的卡车
that a truck carrying three cesium-137 irradiators

219
00:14:13,740 --> 00:14:15,100
未按时到达两个检查站
missed two checkpoints.

220
00:14:15,100 --> 00:14:16,900
卡车本该从亚特兰大
It was supposed to be traveling from Atlanta

221
00:14:16,900 --> 00:14:19,110
驶回巴尔的摩的生产厂商那里
back to the manufacturer in Baltimore.

222
00:14:19,110 --> 00:14:20,620
卡车现在在什么位置
Where do we think the truck is now?

223
00:14:20,620 --> 00:14:22,050
卡车的卫星定位下线了
Truck's GPS is offline.

224
00:14:22,050 --> 00:14:23,610
怎么会出这样的破事
How the hell does a thing like that happen?

225
00:14:23,610 --> 00:14:25,700
-我们得重新评估  -可是该重新评估了
- We'll have to reevaluate. - You're damn right we will.

226
00:14:25,700 --> 00:14:27,390
但我们必须作出决定
But we need to make some decisions.

227
00:14:27,390 --> 00:14:29,920
我们应该通知特区警察和弗州州警
We should notify Metro PD and Virginia State Police.

228
00:14:29,920 --> 00:14:31,460
要不要疏散群众
Are we gonna evacuate the public?

229
00:14:31,460 --> 00:14:32,520
不行  在采取任何行动之前
No. Before we do anything,

230
00:14:32,520 --> 00:14:34,400
我要和反恐处局长谈一谈
I wanna speak to the head of counterterrorism.

231
00:14:34,400 --> 00:14:36,140
给我接助理局长格林
Get Assistant Director Green on the line.

232
00:14:36,140 --> 00:14:38,620
-女士  国安部已经  -总统说得对
- Ma'am, Homeland is over... - The president is right.

233
00:14:39,950 --> 00:14:41,070
女士
Ma'am?

234
00:14:42,570 --> 00:14:43,860
我是安德伍德总统
This is President Underwood.

235
00:14:43,860 --> 00:14:46,270
眼下我们还不清楚谁对这起事件负责
At this time, we have no idea who's responsible.

236
00:14:46,270 --> 00:14:47,450
格林局长  我最好还是
Director Green, perhaps it's better

237
00:14:47,450 --> 00:14:49,650
把你接到免提上  请稍等
I patch you into the whole room. One second.

238
00:14:52,250 --> 00:14:54,960
自从他的轮班开始  司机就失联了
The driver's been unreachable since his shift began.

239
00:14:55,550 --> 00:14:57,100
卡车上的放射物
There's enough radiation on that truck

240
00:14:57,100 --> 00:14:59,210
足够影响方圆50公里左右的区域
to impact a 30-mile radius.

241
00:14:59,290 --> 00:15:01,880
即便不被武器化  也会扩散到大气中
Even if it's not weaponized, it would be in the air,

242
00:15:01,880 --> 00:15:04,430
水里  影响儿童和平民
in the water, children, people...

243
00:15:05,700 --> 00:15:09,770
将军  我在这里都能听见车轮轰轰响了
General, I can hear the wheels grinding from here.

244
00:15:09,780 --> 00:15:11,820
最好还是不要妄加推测  先生
I'd rather not speculate, sir.

245
00:15:12,950 --> 00:15:14,500
请你尽情推测一下
Oh, please do.

246
00:15:16,210 --> 00:15:19,670
过去几天以来  哈里发国的情报越来越多
Over the past several days, there has been increased ICO chatter,

247
00:15:19,670 --> 00:15:21,780
但这已经是新常态了
but that is the new normal.

248
00:15:23,020 --> 00:15:26,450
我们把可能受影响区域的地图和数据发过去了
We've sent over stats and maps of potentially affected areas.

249
00:15:39,740 --> 00:15:41,280
我真不知道哪个更可怕
I don't know what's worse.

250
00:15:41,350 --> 00:15:44,050
是随时会炸的脏弹  还是全城人知道
A dirty bomb about to go off or what'll happen to the city

251
00:15:44,050 --> 00:15:45,460
我们在找一枚脏弹后的反应
when they know we're looking for one.

252
00:15:45,460 --> 00:15:48,460
-上头有谁留守  -赛斯和莉安
- Who do we have left upstairs? - Seth and LeAnn.

253
00:15:49,200 --> 00:15:50,890
你和格林保持通信
You stay in touch with Green.

254
00:15:51,590 --> 00:15:53,630
如果真的有脏弹
If this is a dirty bomb,

255
00:15:53,630 --> 00:15:55,860
那局面可就彻底不一样了
then we've just entered a different world.

256
00:15:56,000 --> 00:15:57,200
好  先生
Yes, sir.

257
00:15:58,660 --> 00:15:59,690
好了  我们继续集中力量
All right, we need to stay focused

258
00:15:59,690 --> 00:16:01,960
制定一份紧急疏散计划
on our contingency plan for an evacuation

259
00:16:01,960 --> 00:16:04,200
但不要让外界察觉我们的行动
without the appearance of doing so.

260
00:16:08,640 --> 00:16:10,430
我们需要准备实施单向...
We need to be ready to implement one way...

261
00:16:10,430 --> 00:16:12,480
给我联系能源部的清理小队...
We need to get the cleanup team from the Energy...

262
00:16:12,480 --> 00:16:15,010
...有权调取安保监控录像....
...whose jurisdiction it is to get the security cams...

263
00:16:18,030 --> 00:16:20,360
没错  最终宣布后
Yes. Whenever it happens,

264
00:16:20,310 --> 00:16:30,310
{\an1}{\pos(113.7,221.85)}汤姆·汉默施密特
《华盛顿先驱报》

265
00:16:20,360 --> 00:16:23,040
这次任命便能打破最高法院的僵局
this appointment would break the court's deadlock.

266
00:16:23,040 --> 00:16:25,380
我们终于能继续推进这次大选了
And we would get this election going again.

267
00:16:25,390 --> 00:16:27,480
但请大家退一步想一想
But let's step back a minute.

268
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:30,410
田纳西已经不重要了
Tennessee is out of the equation.

269
00:16:30,820 --> 00:16:34,000
无论谁赢下田州  都不够取胜
Whoever wins that state, it's not enough.

270
00:16:34,130 --> 00:16:38,580
这样就取决于最后一个州  俄亥俄州
It's come down to one state. Ohio.

271
00:16:38,680 --> 00:16:41,050
一个州的选择  将左右
One state is about to choose

272
00:16:41,050 --> 00:16:44,450
下一任美国总统的人选
the next President of these United States.

273
00:16:44,450 --> 00:16:46,480
我们怎么会让这种事发生
How did we let this happen?

274
00:16:46,750 --> 00:16:48,720
而且还不止一次
And it keeps happening.

275
00:16:48,970 --> 00:16:52,880
这届政府一贯喜欢搞闭门政治
This is an administration that operates behind closed doors,

276
00:16:52,880 --> 00:16:54,730
逃避公共监督
out of the public eye.

277
00:16:54,900 --> 00:16:58,170
今天的突然推迟也是一贯的套路
Today's sudden postponement is typical.

278
00:16:58,170 --> 00:17:00,050
玫瑰园没发表一个字的声明
With no announcement in the Rose Garden,

279
00:17:00,050 --> 00:17:03,620
整个白宫也完全没有任何消息放出
and literally zero news coming from the White House,

280
00:17:03,620 --> 00:17:06,630
我们不得不去想  究竟发生了什么幕后惊变
one has to wonder what is going on behind the scenes

281
00:17:06,630 --> 00:17:09,070
才导致这次意外推迟
to cause this unexpected delay.

282
00:17:09,270 --> 00:17:11,900
白宫的沉默  振聋发聩
The silence is deafening.

283
00:17:12,360 --> 00:17:14,600
在这样一场旷日持久
After such a protracted,

284
00:17:14,600 --> 00:17:17,340
令人疑惑  混乱不堪的选举之后
confusing and, frankly, chaotic election,

285
00:17:17,340 --> 00:17:19,040
我们有权了解真相
we deserve clarity.

286
00:17:19,460 --> 00:17:22,300
可是  又是这样
Instead, here we are again...

287
00:17:22,510 --> 00:17:25,950
我们又被蒙在鼓里  神经紧张
left out of the loop and on the edge of our seats.

288
00:17:26,030 --> 00:17:29,440
我希望美国人民不会习惯了这种现象
I just hope America isn't getting used to this.

289
00:17:32,210 --> 00:17:34,490
-喂  -是我
- Hello? - Hey, it's me.

290
00:17:34,890 --> 00:17:35,720
道格
Doug?

291
00:17:36,110 --> 00:17:37,450
为什么没人告诉我
Why wasn't I read in?

292
00:17:38,350 --> 00:17:40,770
-告诉你什么  -正在发生的事
- To what? - Whatever's going on.

293
00:17:40,770 --> 00:17:43,890
如果总统躲入地堡会对我们有利
If this is gonna play for us, the president in the bunker,

294
00:17:43,890 --> 00:17:45,460
我要知道该如何操作
I need to know how to play it.

295
00:17:45,560 --> 00:17:46,460
有一辆运送
There's a truck carrying

296
00:17:46,470 --> 00:17:48,800
放射性物质的货车失联了
radioactive material that's gone missing.

297
00:17:49,540 --> 00:17:52,660
好  赛斯和我要准备一份声明吗
Okay. Should Seth and I prepare a statement?

298
00:17:52,670 --> 00:17:55,280
-我们要说货车在哪  -不清楚
- Where are we saying the truck is? - We don't know.

299
00:17:56,460 --> 00:17:58,880
-什么时候能找到它  -也不清楚
- When are we gonna find it? - We don't know.

300
00:18:00,160 --> 00:18:02,970
等下  真的有事发生吗
Wait, is something really happening?

301
00:18:03,750 --> 00:18:04,960
可能没有
Probably not.

302
00:18:10,160 --> 00:18:12,610
-喂  -可能没有
- Hello? - Probably not?

303
00:18:12,610 --> 00:18:13,750
那我该做些什么
What am I supposed to do?

304
00:18:14,690 --> 00:18:15,790
-是道格吗  -是的
- Is that Doug? - Yeah.

305
00:18:15,790 --> 00:18:16,820
我能跟他说两句吗
Can I talk to him?

306
00:18:17,380 --> 00:18:19,790
-你能告诉我们什么  -表现如常
- Hey, what can you tell us? - Act normal.

307
00:18:19,790 --> 00:18:20,870
继续关注情势
Stay on point.

308
00:18:20,870 --> 00:18:22,610
只回应正在进行的竞选活动
Comment only on the ongoing campaign.

309
00:18:22,610 --> 00:18:24,690
我已经把他们的日程活动延期了
I've already postponed their scheduled events.

310
00:18:24,690 --> 00:18:27,090
我们现在有危险吗
Look, are we in danger here or what?

311
00:18:28,050 --> 00:18:29,170
我无法回答这个问题
I can't answer.

312
00:18:30,300 --> 00:18:31,580
因为我也不知道
Because I don't know.

313
00:18:32,280 --> 00:18:34,570
静等国安部的进一步指示吧
Await further instructions from Homeland.

314
00:18:35,080 --> 00:18:36,020
好吧
All right.

315
00:18:37,950 --> 00:18:39,540
道格  我们还要留在这儿吗
Doug, should we be here?

316
00:18:41,870 --> 00:18:42,800
他挂了
He hung up.

317
00:18:45,930 --> 00:18:46,920
我们在做什么
What are we doing?

318
00:18:56,880 --> 00:18:59,100
诺拉觉得我们需要通知麦卡锡议长
Nora thinks we need to notify Speaker McCarthy.

319
00:18:59,100 --> 00:19:01,140
我觉得现在谈政府继续运作为时尚早
I think it's too soon for a continuity of government.

320
00:19:01,150 --> 00:19:03,670
如果我们计划撤离  需要通知国会
If we're planning an evacuation, Congress needs to be notified--

321
00:19:03,670 --> 00:19:05,970
我说了  我觉得太早了
I said, I believe it is a bit too early.

322
00:19:05,970 --> 00:19:08,210
总统女士  莫里森总监认为...
Madam President, Director Morrison thinks that--

323
00:19:08,220 --> 00:19:09,820
等下  莫里森总监在哪  为什么...
Wait a minute. Where is Director Morrison? Why--

324
00:19:09,820 --> 00:19:11,420
她选择留在国家情报总监办公室
She opted to stay at ODNI.

325
00:19:11,420 --> 00:19:12,700
她在那里指挥行动
She's monitoring from there.

326
00:19:12,700 --> 00:19:14,080
至少给她打个电话
Well, at least let's get her on the phone.

327
00:19:14,090 --> 00:19:16,630
我们早该在数月前趁有机会时铲除哈里发国
We should have wiped out ICO when we had the chance.

328
00:19:16,630 --> 00:19:19,260
我们没问你的个人意见  将军
We didn't ask for your personal opinion, General.

329
00:19:20,150 --> 00:19:23,340
我们需要了解艾哈迈德·艾哈迈迪的最新情况
What we need is an update on the Ahmed Al Ahmadi situation.

330
00:19:23,430 --> 00:19:25,680
是  女士  我这就去和莫里森总监确认
Yes, ma'am. I'll check with Director Morrison now.

331
00:19:33,910 --> 00:19:35,910
我有一些关系
I have contacts, you know.

332
00:19:36,580 --> 00:19:39,510
本地的私人承包商  也许能帮上忙
Private contractors in the region that might be of help.

333
00:19:39,510 --> 00:19:41,230
你是暗示说你的联系人
Are you suggesting that your contacts

334
00:19:41,230 --> 00:19:43,830
比联调局和国安局知道得还多吗
know more than the Bureau, the NSA--

335
00:19:43,830 --> 00:19:45,640
我没有暗示什么
I'm not suggesting anything.

336
00:19:46,620 --> 00:19:47,860
我是在告诉你
I'm telling you.

337
00:19:48,340 --> 00:19:52,340
我认识和哈里发国谈判过的第三方人士
I know third parties that have negotiated with ICO in the past.

338
00:19:53,080 --> 00:19:56,820
人质之类的事  他们也许知道点什么
Hostages and whatnot... who may know something.

339
00:19:56,820 --> 00:19:58,420
但我需要打个电话
But I need a line.

340
00:20:00,070 --> 00:20:02,210
保密电话
Just a... a secure one.

341
00:20:05,440 --> 00:20:07,470
我在这儿都快透不过气了
I can barely breathe in here.

342
00:20:08,020 --> 00:20:10,470
我去给咱们倒杯咖啡
I'm gonna go get us a cup of coffee.

343
00:20:16,840 --> 00:20:20,210
戴维斯女士怎么会有这么高的安全等级
How does Miss Davis have this level of clearance?

344
00:20:22,570 --> 00:20:24,140
这值得探究
That's a good question.

345
00:20:33,680 --> 00:20:36,440
-我们是不是自作自受  -什么
- Did we bring this on ourselves? - What?

346
00:20:37,770 --> 00:20:39,690
-对不起  我不该这么说的  -听我说
- I'm sorry. I shouldn't have. - Listen to me.

347
00:20:39,690 --> 00:20:41,690
我们所做的一切  一切
Everything we've done, everything,

348
00:20:41,860 --> 00:20:43,840
都是我们必须做的
is exactly what we had to do.

349
00:20:46,180 --> 00:20:47,870
我们都还不知道这是不是真的
We don't even know if this is real.

350
00:21:19,890 --> 00:21:21,530
这是我在香港买的
I get these in Hong Kong.

351
00:21:22,720 --> 00:21:25,940
最好喝的速溶咖啡出自环太平洋地区
The best instant coffee comes out of the Pacific Rim.

352
00:21:29,460 --> 00:21:32,380
-你想来一杯吗  -如果你还有多的
- Would you like one? - If you can spare it.

353
00:21:32,990 --> 00:21:35,350
我包里总是装着三四包
Oh, I always have three or four in my bag.

354
00:21:42,060 --> 00:21:44,120
不知我们要在这里待多久
I wonder how long we'll be down here.

355
00:21:44,970 --> 00:21:46,900
目前情势还不明朗
The situation's still unclear.

356
00:21:49,960 --> 00:21:52,940
我不该喝咖啡的  我还有点站不稳
I shouldn't be drinking coffee. I still feel a little shaky.

357
00:21:57,680 --> 00:21:58,760
你看起来还好
You don't look it.

358
00:22:09,390 --> 00:22:10,540
摸摸我的脉搏
Feel my pulse.

359
00:22:15,750 --> 00:22:18,050
我看你很自若
You seem very much in control to me.

360
00:22:24,920 --> 00:22:25,940
你也是
So do you.

361
00:22:28,130 --> 00:22:30,180
这说明了我们什么
What does that say about the two of us?

362
00:22:53,310 --> 00:22:54,370
好的  谢谢
Yes, thank you.

363
00:22:55,700 --> 00:22:57,930
海豹突击队正在追踪艾哈迈德·艾哈迈迪
The SEAL team is on the trail of Ahmed Al Ahmadi,

364
00:22:57,940 --> 00:22:59,750
但是国家情报局认为
but National Intelligence believes

365
00:22:59,750 --> 00:23:01,630
他发现我们在追踪他了
he's discovered we're following him

366
00:23:01,630 --> 00:23:03,640
而那卡车正是对策
and the truck is a countermeasure.

367
00:23:03,640 --> 00:23:07,240
哈里发国想看到艾哈迈迪完好地走出大马士革
ICO wants to see Ahmadi walking out of Damascus in one piece.

368
00:23:07,240 --> 00:23:09,420
如果我们袭击  他们会反攻
If we strike, they will hit back.

369
00:23:09,420 --> 00:23:11,100
需要启动首都撤离程序
Capital-wide evacuation procedures need to be initiated--

370
00:23:11,100 --> 00:23:13,100
-等等  -我们得首要考虑民众
- Just hold on! - No, the public is our priority--

371
00:23:13,100 --> 00:23:15,740
等等  我想知道袭击的可能性有多大
Hold on! I want to know how close we are to a strike

372
00:23:15,740 --> 00:23:17,150
以及这辆该死的卡车在哪里
and where this goddamn truck is

373
00:23:17,150 --> 00:23:18,660
然后我们再做最后的决定
before we make any final decisions.

374
00:23:18,660 --> 00:23:19,670
"我们再做最后的决定"
"We make any decisions"?

375
00:23:19,670 --> 00:23:21,700
没错  我仍然是
Yes, I am still in a position to make--

376
00:23:21,700 --> 00:23:23,910
如果我错了就纠正我  但你不是
Correct me if I'm wrong, but you are not in a position--

377
00:23:23,910 --> 00:23:27,340
诺拉  敌人不在这里
Nora. The enemy isn't in here.

378
00:23:33,270 --> 00:23:35,490
卡弗蒂说得对  我们应该撤离
Cafferty is right. We should evacuate.

379
00:23:35,490 --> 00:23:37,790
但我想的是将军
But it's the general who's on my mind.

380
00:23:39,410 --> 00:23:40,550
卡弗蒂女士
Miss Cafferty.

381
00:23:40,830 --> 00:23:43,650
我完全失态了  请接受我的道歉
I was entirely out of line. Please accept my apology.

382
00:23:49,220 --> 00:23:50,370
我和戴维斯谈过了
I spoke with Davis.

383
00:23:50,380 --> 00:23:53,680
-怎样  -一无所获  她只是在耍滑头
- And? - Nothing. She was just flexing.

384
00:23:56,740 --> 00:23:57,770
凯茜
Cathy.

385
00:24:05,780 --> 00:24:08,210
今天是谁安排了和克莱尔的会议
Who called a meeting with Claire today?

386
00:24:08,210 --> 00:24:10,230
你还是戴维斯女士
You or Miss Davis?

387
00:24:10,420 --> 00:24:11,450
是简
Jane did.

388
00:24:12,700 --> 00:24:14,200
非常感谢  凯茜
Thank you very much, Cathy.

389
00:24:14,220 --> 00:24:16,280
-没事了吗  -是的  谢谢
- Was that all? - Yes, thank you.

390
00:24:16,640 --> 00:24:18,120
抱歉  还有一件事
Oh, sorry, one more thing.

391
00:24:18,120 --> 00:24:22,290
布雷格什么时候得到第四颗星的  哪届政府
When did Braegher get his fourth star? Which administration?

392
00:24:22,310 --> 00:24:23,630
几届前
A couple back.

393
00:24:23,990 --> 00:24:26,080
他和布洛哈特是一起的吗
So he and Brockhart together?

394
00:24:26,560 --> 00:24:29,800
是的  还有几位也在大概同一时期晋升
And a few others who were elevated around the same time, yes.

395
00:24:29,960 --> 00:24:31,250
谢谢  凯茜
Thank you, Cathy.

396
00:24:37,940 --> 00:24:40,750
我们谈过的那个布洛哈特的料  你拿到了吗
That Brockhart spot we talked about. You have it?

397
00:24:41,600 --> 00:24:42,760
证实了吗
Is it verified?

398
00:24:43,600 --> 00:24:44,480
等等
Hold on.

399
00:24:50,350 --> 00:24:51,280
好了
Ready.

400
00:24:53,210 --> 00:24:54,460
我对天发誓
I swear to God,

401
00:24:54,540 --> 00:24:56,420
要是安德伍德往边境派兵
if Underwood puts soldiers on those borders,

402
00:24:56,420 --> 00:24:58,440
我第一个站出来让军人抗命
I'll be the first to tell them not to listen.

403
00:24:58,800 --> 00:25:02,000
如果美国总统下达那种命令
If the President of the United States gives orders like that,

404
00:25:02,040 --> 00:25:03,770
你就让他早死早超生
you put him out of his misery.

405
00:25:03,770 --> 00:25:05,630
没了  这是全部
That's it. That's all I have.

406
00:25:06,530 --> 00:25:08,340
不  这很好
No, that's good.

407
00:25:08,450 --> 00:25:10,160
如果我们撑过了今天
If we survive the day.

408
00:25:10,400 --> 00:25:12,090
赛斯还和你在办公室吗
Is Seth still in the office with you?

409
00:25:12,150 --> 00:25:15,700
我在总统办公室  坐在坚决桌后
I'm in the Oval, sitting behind the Resolute desk.

410
00:25:16,970 --> 00:25:18,060
你不会的
That's not you.

411
00:25:18,560 --> 00:25:20,910
你总是对我下判断
You know, you keep deciding who I am

412
00:25:21,200 --> 00:25:22,870
却总是误判我
and you keep reading me wrong.

413
00:25:23,330 --> 00:25:25,400
有关于这里发生了什么的谣言吗
Are there rumors about what's going on down here?

414
00:25:25,610 --> 00:25:28,010
有  但我们在应付了
Yes, but we're deflecting.

415
00:25:28,070 --> 00:25:31,170
-康威竞选团队来问过吗  -还没有
- Has the Conway campaign reached out? - Not yet.

416
00:25:31,170 --> 00:25:34,740
将军在俄亥俄州做巡回宣传  州长断联了
The general's on a stump in Ohio and the governor's off the grid.

417
00:25:34,740 --> 00:25:37,220
-好的  继续留意他  -我会的
- Okay. Stay on him. - I will.

418
00:25:38,190 --> 00:25:40,900
除非是世界末日  那就没关系了
Unless it's the end of the world and it doesn't matter.

419
00:25:42,190 --> 00:25:43,850
再见  道格·斯坦普
Goodbye, Doug Stamper.

420
00:25:49,810 --> 00:25:52,680
你确定你该进去那里吗  金发姑娘
Are you sure you should be in there, Goldilocks?

421
00:26:32,880 --> 00:26:34,020
你还好吗
Are you all right?

422
00:26:36,670 --> 00:26:39,810
坦白说  我在想我们在地下多深
Honestly, I was thinking about how far down we are

423
00:26:39,810 --> 00:26:41,590
以及我不喜欢这样
and how it's not my favorite thing.

424
00:26:43,230 --> 00:26:44,950
对不起  你需要进来吗
I... I'm sorry. Do... do you need to be in here?

425
00:26:44,950 --> 00:26:46,510
不不  没关系
No. No, no. It's fine.

426
00:26:48,010 --> 00:26:50,880
我曾经害怕飞行  后来克服了
I used to have a fear of flying, but I got over it.

427
00:26:51,590 --> 00:26:53,670
现在再也不怕了
Doesn't bother me at all anymore.

428
00:26:54,560 --> 00:26:57,390
但我的恐惧似乎转向了另一个方向
But the pendulum seems to have swung the other way.

429
00:26:58,220 --> 00:27:00,660
如果我想太多  会开始有活埋感
If I think too hard, I start to feel buried.

430
00:27:01,090 --> 00:27:04,530
不好意思  室内空气循环让我更加不安了
Forgive me. It's the recirculated air, makes things worse.

431
00:27:07,400 --> 00:27:10,610
戴维斯女士  你为什么会来这儿
Miss Davis, why are you here?

432
00:27:10,710 --> 00:27:13,350
-特勤局带我来的  -不
- This is where the Secret Service led me. - No.

433
00:27:13,570 --> 00:27:17,040
不管是否在准入名单上  你必定是自愿来的
Access list or not, you have to choose to be here.

434
00:27:17,040 --> 00:27:18,910
我总是选择最安全的地方
I always choose the safest place.

435
00:27:18,910 --> 00:27:20,460
你为什么会来这儿
Why are you here?

436
00:27:23,160 --> 00:27:25,060
感觉有机可寻
It felt like an opportunity.

437
00:27:25,870 --> 00:27:28,500
会面的机会  私下会面
A chance for a meeting, not quite on the books.

438
00:27:28,940 --> 00:27:31,460
我刚通完电话  总统女士
I just got off the phone, Madam President.

439
00:27:31,960 --> 00:27:35,400
我有来自国外私人承包商的信息
I have information from abroad, from private contractors...

440
00:27:35,400 --> 00:27:38,160
艾哈迈迪在大马士革
Ahmadi is in Damascus.

441
00:27:38,160 --> 00:27:41,170
多方势力竞相要捉住他
And a number of parties were racing to capture him,

442
00:27:41,400 --> 00:27:43,830
其中当然包括美国
including, of course, the United States.

443
00:27:44,010 --> 00:27:45,310
但是没有人
But no one...

444
00:27:46,440 --> 00:27:48,670
能在今天逮住他
will be capturing him today.

445
00:27:49,680 --> 00:27:51,420
或是在选举前逮住他
Or before the election.

446
00:27:52,560 --> 00:27:54,000
我的职业
I've made a career...

447
00:27:55,170 --> 00:27:57,700
就是处理世界的问题地区
out of dealing with problematic parts of the world.

448
00:28:01,220 --> 00:28:05,710
我的工作  就是想象不可想象之事
It's kind of my vocation to imagine the unimaginable.

449
00:28:10,390 --> 00:28:11,550
失陪了
Excuse me.

450
00:28:18,820 --> 00:28:20,520
-抱歉  -抱歉
- Pardon me. - I'm sorry.

451
00:28:20,520 --> 00:28:22,530
-没事  -失陪了  总统先生
- It's all right. - Excuse me, Mr. President.

452
00:28:28,900 --> 00:28:32,610
我感觉她想把艾哈迈迪献给我们
I had the distinct feeling she was offering Ahmadi to us.

453
00:28:32,610 --> 00:28:33,620
意思是
Meaning?

454
00:28:33,950 --> 00:28:36,670
她说有多方势力正在设法捉住他
She said there are a number of groups looking to capture him,

455
00:28:36,670 --> 00:28:40,570
但在选举之前都不会有人成功
but that no one will. Not today or before the election.

456
00:28:42,270 --> 00:28:44,390
这是我们自找的
We brought this on ourselves.

457
00:28:44,860 --> 00:28:47,380
-我们逼得太紧  -我们存活下来了
- We pushed too hard. - We've survived.

458
00:28:47,380 --> 00:28:50,260
-我们自我孤立了  弗兰西斯  -又如何
- We isolated ourselves, Francis. - So what?

459
00:28:50,680 --> 00:28:51,910
你我都明白一件
We both know something

460
00:28:51,910 --> 00:28:53,670
其他人拒绝承认的事
the rest of the world refuses to acknowledge.

461
00:28:53,670 --> 00:28:56,660
世上没有正义  唯有征服
There is no justice, only conquest.

462
00:28:56,760 --> 00:28:59,340
我告诉你  我们要是准许他们疏散华盛顿
And let me tell you, we let them evacuate D.C.,

463
00:28:59,340 --> 00:29:02,060
我们就没戏了 克莱尔  我们就输了
we are done, Claire. We've lost.

464
00:29:02,760 --> 00:29:03,700
请进
Yes?

465
00:29:07,890 --> 00:29:11,200
我刚和莉安通了话  你们得听听
I just spoke to LeAnn. You need to hear this.

466
00:29:11,720 --> 00:29:12,930
我对天发誓
I swear to God,

467
00:29:13,130 --> 00:29:14,820
要是安德伍德往边境派兵
if Underwood puts soldiers on those borders,

468
00:29:14,820 --> 00:29:16,880
我第一个站出来让军人抗命
I'll be the first to tell them not to listen.

469
00:29:16,990 --> 00:29:20,100
如果美国总统下达那种命令
If the President of the United States gives orders like that,

470
00:29:20,210 --> 00:29:22,050
你就让他早死早超生
you put him out of his misery.

471
00:29:28,620 --> 00:29:29,470
让我出去
Let me out.

472
00:29:29,470 --> 00:29:31,920
-很抱歉  先生  我不能...  -开门
- I'm sorry, sir. I'm not allowed-- - Open the door.

473
00:29:31,920 --> 00:29:34,330
-我奉命...  -我已经不是总统
- My orders are to-- - I am no longer the president.

474
00:29:34,330 --> 00:29:37,590
我已无义务或责任在身  是不是
I have no responsibilities or obligations. Isn't that correct?

475
00:29:37,590 --> 00:29:39,440
解除威胁前我们不能让你出去
We can't send you above until the threat is contained--

476
00:29:39,440 --> 00:29:41,880
-把门打开  -让他出去
- Open this door. - Let him out.

477
00:29:42,680 --> 00:29:45,250
-女士  -让总统出去
- Ma'am? - Let the president out.

478
00:29:47,180 --> 00:29:48,640
把门打开
Open the door.

479
00:29:51,780 --> 00:29:52,640
打开
Open it.

480
00:31:18,560 --> 00:31:19,490
总统女士
Ma'am.

481
00:31:20,320 --> 00:31:22,650
我们必须开始疏散
We need to initiate evacuation now.

482
00:31:22,660 --> 00:31:25,170
不  将军  我说疏散才疏散
No, General. We'll do it when I say so.

483
00:31:32,370 --> 00:31:33,480
真的很抱歉
I'm really sorry.

484
00:31:33,480 --> 00:31:36,850
我知道我答应你了  但我得去接我小孩
I know I agreed to do this, but I have to go pick up my kids.

485
00:31:36,680 --> 00:31:39,310
{\pos(176.7,63.45)}肝癌互助小组

486
00:31:37,210 --> 00:31:39,520
没事  要不我搭你的车
Okay. Well, what if I just rode in the car with you?

487
00:31:39,520 --> 00:31:41,250
家长都在互相发信息
You know, parents are texting one another.

488
00:31:41,250 --> 00:31:42,790
其中一位家长在国安局任职
One of them works at the NSA

489
00:31:42,790 --> 00:31:45,280
他认为有恐袭的可能  所以...
and he thinks there's a terror threat, so...

490
00:31:45,630 --> 00:31:48,570
这事以前也发生过  但...世事难料
I mean, this has happened before, but you just... You never know.

491
00:31:48,800 --> 00:31:52,440
我母亲上个月肾衰竭过世了
My mom died of kidney failure last month.

492
00:31:52,440 --> 00:31:54,190
我很遗憾
Oh, I'm so sorry.

493
00:31:55,490 --> 00:31:56,960
她在候捐名单上吗
Uh, was she on the donor list?

494
00:31:56,960 --> 00:31:59,030
有  但排得不够靠前
Yeah, but not close enough to the top.

495
00:32:01,190 --> 00:32:03,470
你介意吗  我们可以边走边说
Do you mind? You could talk while we walk out of here.

496
00:32:06,730 --> 00:32:08,400
好吧  好
Sure. Yeah.

497
00:32:10,010 --> 00:32:12,160
安东尼病了多久了
Uh, how long was Anthony sick for?

498
00:32:14,910 --> 00:32:17,110
大概两年
About two years.

499
00:32:18,720 --> 00:32:22,700
他一直在抗争  非常顽强  直到最后
And he fought it hard. So hard. The entire way.

500
00:32:25,020 --> 00:32:26,030
{\pos(60.9,40.5)}安东尼·莫雷蒂纪念基金

501
00:32:26,250 --> 00:32:30,290
这地方  只要是现金支付  我就不多问
This unit, if they pay cash, I don't ask questions.

502
00:32:30,790 --> 00:32:33,550
-但你记得那两个年轻女子吧  -当然
- But you remember these young women? - Yeah, of course.

503
00:32:33,840 --> 00:32:36,340
她们非常亲密  如果你明白我的意思
They were very close, if you know what I mean.

504
00:32:37,110 --> 00:32:38,770
但她们很可爱
But they were sweet.

505
00:32:40,530 --> 00:32:44,020
那你有没有见过这个人
And did you ever see... this man?

506
00:32:45,850 --> 00:32:48,050
我不清楚究竟是怎么回事
Look, I don't know what was going on here.

507
00:32:48,050 --> 00:32:49,650
但你认得他吧
But you recognize him?

508
00:32:51,510 --> 00:32:53,530
认得
Yeah. Okay?

509
00:32:54,050 --> 00:32:57,980
是有一个长这样的人预付了三个月房租
Someone looking like him paid the rent. Three months, up-front.

510
00:32:57,980 --> 00:33:00,340
但我说了  我不做评判
But like I said, I don't judge.

511
00:33:05,950 --> 00:33:08,910
我不明白你问的是什么  总统先生
I'm not sure what you're asking, Mr. President.

512
00:33:09,130 --> 00:33:10,960
得了吧
Oh, please.

513
00:33:11,820 --> 00:33:14,460
某个人或者某些人
Someone or someones...

514
00:33:15,160 --> 00:33:17,550
今天想把我和我夫人困在地下
tried to make my wife and I lose the election

515
00:33:17,550 --> 00:33:20,190
好让我们输掉大选
by keeping us underground today.

516
00:33:20,190 --> 00:33:23,550
我想知道你对此有什么了解
And I would like to know what you know about that.

517
00:33:23,880 --> 00:33:26,300
我们都在实时应对
We've all been responding in real time

518
00:33:26,300 --> 00:33:28,140
一起潜在的恐怖袭击
to a potential terrorist attack.

519
00:33:28,140 --> 00:33:29,860
但你选择待在这里
But you chose to stay here.

520
00:33:29,860 --> 00:33:31,900
你怎么不和我们一起去地堡
Why weren't you in the bunker with us?

521
00:33:31,900 --> 00:33:33,960
我选择留在我的办公室
I chose to remain in my office

522
00:33:33,960 --> 00:33:37,320
监督对艾哈迈德·艾哈迈迪的逮捕或击杀
to oversee the capture or killing of one Ahmed Al Ahmadi.

523
00:33:38,610 --> 00:33:40,680
但今天上午  你和布雷格将军
And yet there was great tension this morning

524
00:33:40,680 --> 00:33:42,700
闹得很紧张
between you and General Braegher.

525
00:33:42,700 --> 00:33:44,410
见解不同
Difference in approach.

526
00:33:44,940 --> 00:33:48,060
我们不会疏散哥伦比亚特区的
We are not going to evacuate the District of Columbia.

527
00:33:48,060 --> 00:33:51,590
我要你明白这一点  无论如何
I want you to understand that. Come what may.

528
00:33:53,930 --> 00:33:57,740
另外我向你保证  凡妮莎
And I promise you this... Vanessa.

529
00:33:59,320 --> 00:34:02,050
等我查明真相
When I find out exactly what has happened,

530
00:34:02,050 --> 00:34:04,770
我会记得这次对话
I'm going to remember this conversation,

531
00:34:04,770 --> 00:34:08,180
我会记得  你选择了隐瞒信息
when you chose to withhold information.

532
00:34:09,180 --> 00:34:13,680
布雷格将军是布洛哈特将军的强烈支持者
General Braegher is a strong supporter of General Brockhart.

533
00:34:17,600 --> 00:34:19,120
他们串通了吗
Did they conspire?

534
00:34:23,680 --> 00:34:27,490
他们是不是想利用恐怖
Did they use... terror...

535
00:34:27,770 --> 00:34:30,280
和此次疏散
and this evacuation

536
00:34:30,430 --> 00:34:33,700
让我输掉这场大选
to cost me this election?

537
00:34:34,810 --> 00:34:37,150
我并不喜欢将军这个人
I'm not a fan of the general...

538
00:34:38,620 --> 00:34:41,650
但这是个严重的指控
but... that's a strong charge,

539
00:34:41,660 --> 00:34:43,320
而且没有任何证据支撑
and there's no proof to support it.

540
00:34:45,260 --> 00:34:48,580
你们这些人最擅长保护的  是彼此
You know, what you people protect best is each other.

541
00:34:49,060 --> 00:34:52,080
艾哈迈迪不久前没了踪迹
We lost Ahmadi a short time ago

542
00:34:52,090 --> 00:34:54,570
我们相信他已经不在大马士革了
and believe he is no longer in Damascus.

543
00:34:57,130 --> 00:34:58,200
当然了
Of course.

544
00:34:59,580 --> 00:35:00,910
当然了
Of course.

545
00:35:06,440 --> 00:35:08,140
你听好了
Now you listen to me...

546
00:35:09,620 --> 00:35:11,330
这就是一次
This was nothing more or less

547
00:35:11,330 --> 00:35:14,980
明明白白的政变未遂
than an attempted coup, plain and simple.

548
00:35:15,780 --> 00:35:19,870
我不知道你直接参与的程度多深
And I do not know to what degree you have been directly involved.

549
00:35:20,300 --> 00:35:22,990
但你必须化解它
But you will resolve it.

550
00:35:23,820 --> 00:35:25,060
立即化解
Now.

551
00:35:26,510 --> 00:35:28,630
听明白了吗
Do I make myself clear?

552
00:35:31,970 --> 00:35:32,910
明白了  先生
Yes, sir.

553
00:35:47,790 --> 00:35:49,430
卡车找到了
The truck's been found.

554
00:35:50,180 --> 00:35:51,330
我们还不确定
Now we can't know for sure,

555
00:35:51,330 --> 00:35:53,970
但似乎哈里发国没有参与其中
but it looks as though ICO wasn't involved.

556
00:35:53,970 --> 00:35:56,430
辐照器和铯都已找到
The irradiators and cesium were accounted for.

557
00:35:56,430 --> 00:35:58,740
卡车偶然停在了
The truck was accidentally parked

558
00:35:58,740 --> 00:36:01,090
达勒姆的一处医疗设备厂
at a medical device factory in Durham.

559
00:36:01,090 --> 00:36:03,890
工头没有上报
The plant foreman never reported it.

560
00:36:03,920 --> 00:36:06,130
所以我们暂时可以松口气了
So we can relax for now, at least.

561
00:36:06,130 --> 00:36:08,710
感谢大家的付出  谢谢你们
I just wanna thank you all for your efforts. Thank you.

562
00:36:13,290 --> 00:36:16,870
总统女士  我明天一早就递交辞呈
Madam President. You'll have my resignation in the morning.

563
00:36:17,270 --> 00:36:18,190
诺拉
Nora...

564
00:36:19,450 --> 00:36:22,030
今天这是极端情况
these were extraordinary circumstances today.

565
00:36:22,170 --> 00:36:23,580
如果我们丝毫不容忍人为疏忽
What would our administration be

566
00:36:23,580 --> 00:36:26,010
那我们政府成什么了
if we didn't allow for some human failings?

567
00:36:34,940 --> 00:36:36,970
准备发布会  我们马上上去
Get the presser going. We're coming up now.

568
00:36:37,780 --> 00:36:39,510
关于艾哈迈迪
Concerning Ahmadi...

569
00:36:40,360 --> 00:36:41,640
我们没找到他
We didn't find him.

570
00:36:42,140 --> 00:36:44,300
会找到的  你们可以的
You will. You can.

571
00:36:44,300 --> 00:36:46,490
-你有什么提议  -我可以帮忙
- What are you offering? - Help.

572
00:36:47,300 --> 00:36:49,800
如果您愿意  总统女士
If you'd like it, Madam President.

573
00:36:58,460 --> 00:37:00,880
你能详细说明一下今天早些时候的演习吗
Can you elaborate on the drill earlier today?

574
00:37:00,900 --> 00:37:02,590
演习时常进行
Well, drills happen all the time.

575
00:37:02,700 --> 00:37:04,740
这是政府为了保证国家安全
It's part of the administration's ongoing efforts

576
00:37:04,740 --> 00:37:05,790
做的不懈努力
to keep the country safe.

577
00:37:05,790 --> 00:37:08,560
-是  但通常都会提前提醒  -那意义何在
- Yes, but there's usually a warning. - What's the point of that?

578
00:37:09,870 --> 00:37:11,590
-下一位  -赛斯
- Who's next? - Seth.

579
00:37:24,590 --> 00:37:25,880
你看档案了吗
Did you look at the file?

580
00:37:27,290 --> 00:37:28,380
不用看
I didn't have to.

581
00:37:30,630 --> 00:37:32,420
我希望一小时内
I'll expect your signature

582
00:37:32,420 --> 00:37:34,790
收到你签名的辞职信
on the resignation letter within the hour.

583
00:37:36,410 --> 00:37:39,400
除非你选择指出其他涉事的人
Unless you choose to implicate whoever else was involved.

584
